atic}} | Democrat\n|\n|-\n|55th\n|[[William M. Steinfeldt]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Republican\n|\n|-\n|56th\n|[[Jess J. Present]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Republican\n|\n|-\n|57th\n|[[William Stachowski]]*\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} | Democrat\n|\n|-\n|58th\n|[[Anthony M. Masiello]]*\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} | Dem./Lib.\n|\n|-\n|59th\n|[[Dale M. Volker]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./Cons./RTL\n|\n|-\n|60th\n|[[Walter J. Floss Jr.]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./Cons./RTL\n|\n|-\n|61st\n|[[John B. Daly (New York)|John B. Daly]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./Cons.\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n===Employees===\n* Secretary: [[Stephen F. Sloan]]\n\n==State Assembly==\n\n===Assemblymen===\nThe asterisk (*) denotes members of the previous Legislature who continued in office as members of this Legislature.\n\n'''Note:''' For brevity, the chairmanships omit the words \"...the Committee on (the)...\"\n\n{| class=wikitable\n! District\n! Assemblymen\n! Party\n! Notes\n|- \n|1st\n|[[Joseph Sawicki Jr.]]\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./RTL\n|\n|-\n|2nd\n|[[John L. Behan]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./Cons./RTL\n|\n|- \n|3rd\n|[[Icilio W. Bianchi, Jr.]]*\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} | Democrat\n|\n|-\n|4th\n|[[George J. Hochbrueckner]]*\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} | Democrat\n|\n|- \n|5th\n|[[Paul E. Harenberg]]*\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} | Democrat\n|\n|-\n|6th\n|[[Robert C. Wertz]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./Cons./RTL\n|\n|-\n|7th\n|[[Thomas F. Barraga]]\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./Cons./RTL\n|\n|- \n|8th\n|[[John C. Cochrane (politician)|John C. Cochrane]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./Cons.\n|\n|-\n|9th\n|[[John J. Flanagan, Sr.|John J. Flanagan]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./Cons./RTL\n|\n|-\n|10th\n|[[Toni Rettaliata]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./Cons.\n|Chairwoman of the Minority Steering Committee\n|- \n|11th\n|[[Patrick G. Halpin]]*\n|{{Party shading/D