an]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./Lib.\n|\n|-\n|27th\n|[[Manfred Ohrenstein]]*\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} | Dem./Lib.\n|Minority Leader\n|-\n|28th\n|[[Franz S. Leichter]]*\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} | Dem./Lib.\n|\n|-\n|29th\n|[[Leon Bogues]]*\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} | Dem./Lib.\n|\n|-\n|30th\n|[[Olga A. M\u00e9ndez]]*\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} | Dem./Lib.\n|\n|-\n|31st\n|[[Joseph L. Galiber]]*\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} | Dem./Lib.\n|\n|-\n|32nd\n|[[Israel Ruiz, Jr.]]*\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} | Dem./Lib.\n|\n|-\n|33rd\n|[[Abraham Bernstein (politician)|Abraham Bernstein]]*\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} | Dem./Lib.\n|\n|-\n|34th\n|[[John D. Calandra]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./Cons./RTL\n|\n|-\n|35th\n|[[John E. Flynn]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./Cons./RTL\n|\n|-\n|36th\n|[[Joseph R. Pisani]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./Cons.\n|resigned on June 27, 1984<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1984/06/28/nyregion/albany-leaders-draft-a-proposal-on-malpractice.html ''ALBANY LEADERS DRAFT A PROPOSAL ON MALPRACTICE''] in the ''[[New York Times]]'' on June 28, 1984</ref>\n|-\n|37th\n|[[Mary B. Goodhue]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./Cons.\n|\n|-\n|38th\n|[[Linda Winikow]]*\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} | Dem./Lib.\n|\n|-\n|39th\n|[[Richard E. Schermerhorn]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./Cons./RTL\n|\n|-\n|40th\n|[[Charles D. Cook]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./Cons.\n|\n|-\n|41st\n|[[Jay P. Rolison, Jr.]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./Cons.\n|\n|-\n|42nd\n|[[Howard C. Nolan, Jr.]]*\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} | Dem./Lib.\n|\n|-\n|43rd\n|[[Joseph Bruno]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./Cons.\n|\n|-\n|44th\n|[[Hugh T. Farley]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./Cons./RTL\n|\n|-\n|45th\n|[[Ronald B. Stafford]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./Cons.\n|\n|-\n|46th\n|[[Hugh Douglas Barclay]]*\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} | Rep./Cons.\n|\n|-\n|47th\n|[[