{"title_page": "Express Raja", "text_new": "{{Use Indian English|date=November 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Express Raja\n| image          = Express Raja Telugu film Poster.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| film name      = <!--(for non-English films: film's name in its native language)-->\n| director       = [[Merlapaka Gandhi]]\n| producer       = V. Vamsi Krishna Reddy<br>Pramod Uppalapati \n| writer         = [[Merlapaka Gandhi]]\n| screenplay     = [[Merlapaka Gandhi]] and Sheik Dawood G\n| story          = [[Merlapaka Gandhi]]\n| based on       = <!-- {{based on|title of the original work|writer of the original work}} -->\n| starring       = {{unbulleted list|[[Sharwanand]]|[[Surbhi]]|[[Harish Uthaman]]}}\n| narrator       = <!-- or: |narrators = -->\n| music          = Praveen Lakkaraju \n| cinematography = [[Karthik Ghattamaneni]]\n| editing        = \n| studio         = [[UV Creations]]\n| distributor    = <!-- or: |distributors = -->\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2016|01|14}}\n| runtime        = 150 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Telugu\n| budget         = <!--Must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No faceless blogs. No IMDB. See WP:RS-->\n| gross          = {{INRConvert|30|c}}<ref>[http://andhraboxoffice.com/info.aspx?id=1898&cid=6&fid=3268 Express Raja Final Total WW Collections] - ''AndhraBoxOffice'' 10 March 2016</ref>\n}}\n'''''Express Raja''''' is a 2016 Indian [[Telugu language|Telugu]]-language [[comedy]] [[Thriller (genre)|thriller]] film written and directed by [[Merlapaka Gandhi]]. Produced by V. Vamsi Krishna Reddy and Pramod Uppalapati under their production company [[UV Creations]], ''Express Raja'' features [[Sharwanand]] and [[Surbhi]] in the lead roles with [[Harish Uthaman]], Prabhas Sreenu, [[Sapthagiri]], and [[Brahmaji]] in the supporting roles. The film was released worldwide on 14 January 2016 coinciding with the festival of [[Makar Sankranti|Sankranthi]].\n\n==Plot==\nThe film begins with the introduction of Inumu ([[Dhanraj (Telugu comedian)|Dhanraj]]), a peculiar thief who only steals items made out of iron. Then Raja ([[Sharwanand]]), Sreenu (Prabhas Sreenu) and Giri ([[Saptagiri (Telugu actor)|Saptagiri]]) are shown kidnapping a pet dog and escaping. The film then moves to flashback where Raja and Sreenu are both jobless and constant source of irritation for their respective fathers. Raja's father is a teacher and a social activist. He along with his friend ([[Surya (Telugu actor)|Surya]]) collect money for an NGO for treating children. Raja and Sreenu are rounded off by the local area inspector ([[Posani Krishna Murali|Posani]]) for being vagabonds as he feels vagabonds are a nuisance to the society. He orders them to leave for Hyderabad to do jobs that he arranged for them. However, as they reach Hyderabad, Raja sees Amulya ([[Surbhi]]) and falls for her immediately. He then presents himself as a salesman for Oxford Dictionary to woo her. He finally wins her love when he saves her from being molested by some goons. Amulya loves pet dogs while Raja hates them. As fate would have it, Amulya, who was about to propose her love for Raja, sees Raja hand over her pet dog to the local Municipal corporation. An enraged Amulya breaks up with Raja. Raja, to win back her love, goes looking for the dog and finds it in a pet shop, whose owner insists to pay money in exchange. Raja and Seenu, short of money, sell a record number of dictionaries to impress Bill Gates ([[Brahmaji]]) and take the required money from him. On reaching the pet shop, their bag gets exchanged in a bedlam at pet shop with Giri's bag. After a belated realization, they search for Giri and find out that Giri has set the bag on fire thinking that the bag had contained the love letters his sister received. Giri apologises and promises to do whatever Raja and Seenu ask him to. All of them then go to the pet shop only to realize that the dog had already been purchased. They then begin searching for the dog, After few attempts in vain they find the dog in Binami British ([[Supreeth|Supreet]])'s home. The film is taken back to the kidnapping scene where they flee the place after kidnapping the dog. \n\nRaja delivers the dog to Amulya only to find out that she will marry Kesava Reddy ([[Harish Uthaman]]), son of an MLA in Nellore, Kokila ([[Urvashi (actress)|Urvashi]]). A crestfallen Raja is detained by Binami British to reveal the location of the dog. However, Raja and Seenu escape from the clutches of Binami British to Nellore. However, he is caught by Kesava Reddy's gang as soon as he reaches there as Kesava Reddy thinks Raja is the reason behind mother losing her memory during a car crash that occurred in the melee created by the dog kidnapping. Raja is let off by Kesava Reddy as he was admonished by his mother to not to commit any crime until his marriage. Raja, with the help of Sreenu, then reaches the place where Amulya is staying and elopes with her. Keshava Reddy comes to know and chases Raja. Raja encounters a dance troupe on the way only to find that he was using the troupe's vehicle to escape from British. They then reach a local fair where they were to perform in dance program only to be caught by Kesava Reddy on stage. However, the stage where the troupe was dancing collapses due to a mischief by Inumu and Amulya is taken hostage by British and Giri while Kesava Reddy is looking to avenge his mother's memory loss and his abandoned marriage. Raja and Sreenu manage to find the pet dog and hand it over to British in exchange for Amulya. However, all of them are detained by Kesava Reddy only to be rescued by Raja when he knocks out Kesava Reddy using Oxford Dictionary.\n\n==Cast==\n{{colbegin}}\n*[[Sharwanand]] as Raja\n*[[Surbhi]] as Amulya\n*[[Harish Uthaman]] as Keshav Reddy\n*[[Saptagiri (Telugu actor)|Saptagiri]] as Giri\n*[[Urvashi (actress)|Urvashi]] as Kokila \n*[[Nagineedu]] as Raja's father\n*[[Prabhas Sreenu]] as Raja's friend\n*[[Dhanraj (Telugu comedian)|Dhanraj]] as Inumu\n*[[Brahmaji]] as Bill Gates\n*[[Shakalaka Shankar]]\n*[[Posani Krishna Murali]] as police\n*[[Supreeth]] as Binami British\n* Revathi as Amulya's sister\n* Kalpalatha\n* Raghu (choreographer)\n* Duvavsi Mohan\n{{colend}}\n\n==Production==\nIn January 2015, it was announced that Sharwanand was cast in a lead role,<ref name=\"Deccan Chronicle 01-27-15\">{{cite news|last1=staff|title=Merlapaka Gandhi, Sharwanand now join hands|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150127/entertainment-tollywood/article/merlapaka-gandhi-sharwanand-now-join-hands|accessdate=29 September 2015|publisher=[[Deccan Chronicle]]|date=27 January 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Bangalore Mirror 06-02-15\">{{cite news|last1=Kamal|first1=S S|title=Sharwanand Dreams Big Under Prabhas\u2019 Banner|url=http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/Sharwanand-dreams-big-under-Prabhas-banner/articleshow/47517402.cms|accessdate=29 September 2015|publisher=[[Bangalore Mirror]]|date=2 June 2015}}</ref> and later [[Adah Sharma]] was announced as under consideration for the role of the film's lead female,<ref name=\"Andhra Headlines\">{{cite news|last1=staff|title=Ra...ra...Express Raja...|url=http://www.andhraheadlines.com/news/movies/145770/ra-ra-express-raja|accessdate=29 September 2015|publisher=Andhra Headlines|date=2015}}</ref> but Surabhi was the one eventually cast.<ref name=\"Sakshi 09-22-15\">{{cite web|last1=staff|title=\u0c0e\u0c15\u0c4d\u0c38\u0c4d \u0c2a\u0c4d\u0c30\u0c46\u0c38\u0c4d \u0c30\u0c3e\u0c1c\u0c3e'\u0c17\u0c3e \u0c36\u0c30\u0c4d\u0c35\u0c3e\u0c28\u0c02\u0c26\u0c4d|url=http://www.sakshi.com/news/movies/sharwanand-new-film-express-raja-278161|language=Telugu|publisher=[[Sakshi (newspaper)|Sakshi]] |accessdate=29 September 2015|date=22 September 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2015, it was reported that the filming of a few key scenes with the lead cast were under way in areas of [[ameerpet]], [[Hyderabad]].<ref name=\"Today23 News & Analysis 06-14-15\">{{cite news|last1=staff|title=\u2018Run Raja Run\u2019 star Sharwanand\u2019s next film titled \u2018Express Raja\u2019|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-run-raja-run-star-sharwanand-s-next-film-titled-express-raja-2125112|accessdate=29 September 2015|publisher=[[Daily News & Analysis]]|date=14 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Express Raja\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       =  Praveen Lakkaraju\n| cover        = \n| released     = 19th December, 2015\n| recorded     = 2015\n| genre        = [[Soundtrack]]\n| length       = 14:08\n| label        = [[Aditya Music]]\n| producer     =  Praveen Lakkaraju\n| prev_title   = [[Sankarabharanam (2015 film)|Sankarabharanam]]\n| prev_year    = 2015\n| next_title   = [[Luckunnodu]]\n| next_year    = 2017\n}}\n\nThe music was composed by Praveen Lakkaraju and Released on Aditya Music. The audio launch was  held at [[Shilpakala Vedika]] in Hyderabad on December 19. [[Prabhas]], [[Sharwanand]], Surabhi, Vamsi, Pramod, [[Merlapaka Gandhi]], Sujith, Radha Krishna, Brahmaji, [[Saptagiri (actor)|Saptagiri]], [[Maruthi Dasari]], Bunny Vasu, [[Dil Raju]], Supreeth and Satya and some others graced the event. Prabhas launched the big CD and theatrical trailer and presented the first CD to Dil Raju.<ref>{{cite web |title=Photos: Express Raja Audio Release - Sharwanand, Surbhi, Prabhas |url=http://www.ragalahari.com/functions/58533/express-raja-audio-release-photos.aspx |accessdate=7 November 2018 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n{{tracklist|\n|extra_column=Singer(s)\n|headline = Track-List\n|total_length=14:08\n|title1=Hulala|extra1=Sweekar Agasthi, Silvia Anisha | lyrics1 = [[Sri Mani]]|length1=3:43\n|title2= Colorful Chilaka|extra2=Narendra| lyrics2 = [[Bhaskarabhatla Ravi Kumar]]|length2=3:49\n|title3=Ee Vintha Needhiga|extra3=Lipsika, [[Yazin Nizar]]| lyrics3 = Sreejo|length3=2:55\n|title4=24/7 Party|extra4=Yazin Nizar| lyrics4 = Sreejo|length4=3:41\n}}\n\n===Reception===\n{{Album ratings\n| title = Music Review\n| rev1 = IndiaGlitz\n| rev1score = {{Rating|3.25|5}}<ref name=\"IndiaGlitz\">{{cite web |title=Express Raja Music review songs lyrics - IndiaGlitz.com |url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/express-raja-songs-review-telugu-movie-20291 |website=IndiaGlitz.com |accessdate=7 November 2018}}</ref>\n}}\nThe Songs were well received by critics and audience alike.\n\nIndiaglitz in its review states that \"The album makes a terrific impact with two songs - Hulala and Colorful Chilaka, while the other two songs merely pass the muster.  A good choice of singers and a handful of 'hulala' lyrics are the album's biggest strength.\"<ref>{{cite web |title=Express Raja Music review songs lyrics - IndiaGlitz.com |url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/express-raja-songs-review-telugu-movie-20291 |website=IndiaGlitz.com |accessdate=7 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\n''Express Raja'' has been released in close to 500 screens worldwide alongside Balakrishna's ''[[Dictator (2016 film)|Dictator]]''.\n\n==Box office==\n\n===Domestic===\n''Express Raja'' grossed \u20b94 crore on opening day at AP/Telangana box office and has become the biggest opener for Sharwanand.<ref>[http://www.ibtimes.co.in/box-office-collection-nannaku-prematho-business-affected-by-dictator-express-raja-2nd-day-663351 Box office collection: Nannaku Prematho business affected by Dictator, Express Raja on 2nd day]</ref>\n\n===Overseas===\n''Express Raja'' collected US$170,312[\u20b9 1.15 crore] in its extended weekend at the United States. It also done decent business in other parts of the globe, where it is estimated to have grossed \u20b92 crore. The movie has collected approximately \u20b98 crore at the worldwide box office in the first weekend.<ref>[http://www.ibtimes.co.in/express-raja-1st-weekend-box-office-collection-sharwanands-film-earns-rs-5-crore-4-days-663639 Express Raja 1st weekend box office collection: Sharwanand's film earns Rs 5 crore in 4 days]</ref> Express Raja\" collected $315,547 at the US box office in two weeks. According to trade analyst [[Taran Adarsh]] the film has collected $413,324 (\u20b9 2.81 crore) at the US box office in 3 weeks.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/express-raja-us-box-office-collection-sharwanands-film-fares-better-sars-lol-3rd-weekend-665400 |title='Express Raja' US box office collection: Sharwanand's film fares better than 'SARS', 'LOL' in 3rd weekend |access-date=2 March 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160214143942/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/express-raja-us-box-office-collection-sharwanands-film-fares-better-sars-lol-3rd-weekend-665400 |archive-date=14 February 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|5340534}}\n\n[[Category:Telugu-language films]]\n[[Category:2016 films]]\n[[Category:Indian romance films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s Telugu-language films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Indian English|date=November 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Express Raja\n| image          = Express Raja Telugu film Poster.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| film name      = <!--(for non-English films: film's name in its native language)-->\n| director       = [[Merlapaka Gandhi]]\n| producer       = V. Vamsi Krishna Reddy<br>Pramod Uppalapati \n| writer         = [[Merlapaka Gandhi]]\n| screenplay     = [[Merlapaka Gandhi]] and Sheik Dawood G\n| story          = [[Merlapaka Gandhi]]\n| based on       = <!-- {{based on|title of the original work|writer of the original work}} -->\n| starring       = {{unbulleted list|[[Sharwanand]]|[[Surbhi]]|[[Harish Uthaman]]}}\n| narrator       = <!-- or: |narrators = -->\n| music          = Praveen Lakkaraju \n| cinematography = [[Karthik Ghattamaneni]]\n| editing        = \n| studio         = [[UV Creations]]\n| distributor    = <!-- or: |distributors = -->\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2016|01|14}}\n| runtime        = 150 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Telugu\n| budget         = <!--Must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No faceless blogs. No IMDB. See WP:RS-->\n| gross          = {{INRConvert|30|c}}<ref>[http://andhraboxoffice.com/info.aspx?id=1898&cid=6&fid=3268 Express Raja Final Total WW Collections] - ''AndhraBoxOffice'' 10 March 2016</ref>\n}}\n'''''Express Raja''''' is a 2016 Indian [[Telugu language|Telugu]]-language [[comedy]] [[Thriller(genre)|thriller]] film written and directed by [[Merlapaka Gandhi]]. Produced by V. Vamsi Krishna Reddy and Pramod Uppalapati under their production company [[UV Creations]], ''Express Raja'' features [[Sharwanand]] and [[Surbhi]] in the lead roles with [[Harish Uthaman]], Prabhas Sreenu, [[Sapthagiri]], and [[Brahmaji]] in the supporting roles. The film was released worldwide on 14 January 2016 coinciding with the festival of [[Makar Sankranti|Sankranthi]].\n\n==Plot==\nThe film begins with the introduction of Inumu ([[Dhanraj (Telugu comedian)|Dhanraj]]), a peculiar thief who only steals items made out of iron. Then Raja ([[Sharwanand]]), Sreenu (Prabhas Sreenu) and Giri ([[Saptagiri (Telugu actor)|Saptagiri]]) are shown kidnapping a pet dog and escaping. The film then moves to flashback where Raja and Sreenu are both jobless and constant source of irritation for their respective fathers. Raja's father is a teacher and a social activist. He along with his friend ([[Surya (Telugu actor)|Surya]]) collect money for an NGO for treating children. Raja and Sreenu are rounded off by the local area inspector ([[Posani Krishna Murali|Posani]]) for being vagabonds as he feels vagabonds are a nuisance to the society. He orders them to leave for Hyderabad to do jobs that he arranged for them. However, as they reach Hyderabad, Raja sees Amulya ([[Surbhi]]) and falls for her immediately. He then presents himself as a salesman for Oxford Dictionary to woo her. He finally wins her love when he saves her from being molested by some goons. Amulya loves pet dogs while Raja hates them. As fate would have it, Amulya, who was about to propose her love for Raja, sees Raja hand over her pet dog to the local Municipal corporation. An enraged Amulya breaks up with Raja. Raja, to win back her love, goes looking for the dog and finds it in a pet shop, whose owner insists to pay money in exchange. Raja and Seenu, short of money, sell a record number of dictionaries to impress Bill Gates ([[Brahmaji]]) and take the required money from him. On reaching the pet shop, their bag gets exchanged in a bedlam at pet shop with Giri's bag. After a belated realization, they search for Giri and find out that Giri has set the bag on fire thinking that the bag had contained the love letters his sister received. Giri apologises and promises to do whatever Raja and Seenu ask him to. All of them then go to the pet shop only to realize that the dog had already been purchased. They then begin searching for the dog, After few attempts in vain they find the dog in Binami British ([[Supreeth|Supreet]])'s home. The film is taken back to the kidnapping scene where they flee the place after kidnapping the dog. \n\nRaja delivers the dog to Amulya only to find out that she will marry Kesava Reddy ([[Harish Uthaman]]), son of an MLA in Nellore, Kokila ([[Urvashi (actress)|Urvashi]]). A crestfallen Raja is detained by Binami British to reveal the location of the dog. However, Raja and Seenu escape from the clutches of Binami British to Nellore. However, he is caught by Kesava Reddy's gang as soon as he reaches there as Kesava Reddy thinks Raja is the reason behind mother losing her memory during a car crash that occurred in the melee created by the dog kidnapping. Raja is let off by Kesava Reddy as he was admonished by his mother to not to commit any crime until his marriage. Raja, with the help of Sreenu, then reaches the place where Amulya is staying and elopes with her. Keshava Reddy comes to know and chases Raja. Raja encounters a dance troupe on the way only to find that he was using the troupe's vehicle to escape from British. They then reach a local fair where they were to perform in dance program only to be caught by Kesava Reddy on stage. However, the stage where the troupe was dancing collapses due to a mischief by Inumu and Amulya is taken hostage by British and Giri while Kesava Reddy is looking to avenge his mother's memory loss and his abandoned marriage. Raja and Sreenu manage to find the pet dog and hand it over to British in exchange for Amulya. However, all of them are detained by Kesava Reddy only to be rescued by Raja when he knocks out Kesava Reddy using Oxford Dictionary.\n\n==Cast==\n{{colbegin}}\n*[[Sharwanand]] as Raja\n*[[Surbhi]] as Amulya\n*[[Harish Uthaman]] as Keshav Reddy\n*[[Saptagiri (Telugu actor)|Saptagiri]] as Giri\n*[[Urvashi (actress)|Urvashi]] as Kokila \n*[[Nagineedu]] as Raja's father\n*[[Prabhas Sreenu]] as Raja's friend\n*[[Dhanraj (Telugu comedian)|Dhanraj]] as Inumu\n*[[Brahmaji]] as Bill Gates\n*[[Shakalaka Shankar]]\n*[[Posani Krishna Murali]] as police\n*[[Supreeth]] as Binami British\n* Revathi as Amulya's sister\n* Kalpalatha\n* Raghu (choreographer)\n* Duvavsi Mohan\n{{colend}}\n\n==Production==\nIn January 2015, it was announced that Sharwanand was cast in a lead role,<ref name=\"Deccan Chronicle 01-27-15\">{{cite news|last1=staff|title=Merlapaka Gandhi, Sharwanand now join hands|url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/150127/entertainment-tollywood/article/merlapaka-gandhi-sharwanand-now-join-hands|accessdate=29 September 2015|publisher=[[Deccan Chronicle]]|date=27 January 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Bangalore Mirror 06-02-15\">{{cite news|last1=Kamal|first1=S S|title=Sharwanand Dreams Big Under Prabhas\u2019 Banner|url=http://www.bangaloremirror.com/entertainment/south-masala/Sharwanand-dreams-big-under-Prabhas-banner/articleshow/47517402.cms|accessdate=29 September 2015|publisher=[[Bangalore Mirror]]|date=2 June 2015}}</ref> and later [[Adah Sharma]] was announced as under consideration for the role of the film's lead female,<ref name=\"Andhra Headlines\">{{cite news|last1=staff|title=Ra...ra...Express Raja...|url=http://www.andhraheadlines.com/news/movies/145770/ra-ra-express-raja|accessdate=29 September 2015|publisher=Andhra Headlines|date=2015}}</ref> but Surabhi was the one eventually cast.<ref name=\"Sakshi 09-22-15\">{{cite web|last1=staff|title=\u0c0e\u0c15\u0c4d\u0c38\u0c4d \u0c2a\u0c4d\u0c30\u0c46\u0c38\u0c4d \u0c30\u0c3e\u0c1c\u0c3e'\u0c17\u0c3e \u0c36\u0c30\u0c4d\u0c35\u0c3e\u0c28\u0c02\u0c26\u0c4d|url=http://www.sakshi.com/news/movies/sharwanand-new-film-express-raja-278161|language=Telugu|publisher=[[Sakshi (newspaper)|Sakshi]] |accessdate=29 September 2015|date=22 September 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2015, it was reported that the filming of a few key scenes with the lead cast were under way in areas of [[ameerpet]], [[Hyderabad]].<ref name=\"Today23 News & Analysis 06-14-15\">{{cite news|last1=staff|title=\u2018Run Raja Run\u2019 star Sharwanand\u2019s next film titled \u2018Express Raja\u2019|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-run-raja-run-star-sharwanand-s-next-film-titled-express-raja-2125112|accessdate=29 September 2015|publisher=[[Daily News & Analysis]]|date=14 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Express Raja\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       =  Praveen Lakkaraju\n| cover        = \n| released     = 19th December, 2015\n| recorded     = 2015\n| genre        = [[Soundtrack]]\n| length       = 14:08\n| label        = [[Aditya Music]]\n| producer     =  Praveen Lakkaraju\n| prev_title   = [[Sankarabharanam (2015 film)|Sankarabharanam]]\n| prev_year    = 2015\n| next_title   = [[Lucku